        authenticityMarker: "The newspaper-covered table, the communal turning-out of the crabs in a single aromatic heap, and the individual hand-picking with wooden mallets is the Chesapeake crab feast format that has defined summer eating on the Bay since watermen began selling live crabs to shore-side buyers in the late nineteenth century. Serving crabs on plates or providing picks and crackers is considered an outsider adaptation."
